records.addlTxt: Defendant Gabrielle L Fischer in court.  Michael Davis Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.
At the request of the probation agent, the 6/27/14 probation review is rescheduled to 7/18/14 at 1:30 pm.  rmm

Defendant Gabrielle L Fischer in court with attorney Bridget J. Krause.  Matthew J. Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant sentenced to serve 60 days consecutive in the House of Correction with credit for 4 days time served.  
.
AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant sentenced to serve 60 days consecutive in the House of Correction with credit for 0 days time served.  
*
COURT STAYED THE SENTENCES and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 months.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction.  This time is stayed pending a review on 6/27/14.
-Mental Health Evaluation and take ALL prescribed medication, and/or any treatment deemed appropriate.        
-Continue with treatment at LaCausa.
-Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including random screens.
-Maintain absolute sobriety.
-Successfully complete any other counseling and/or treatment deemed appropriate.
-Cooperate with all children's court orders.
-No contact with victim, UNLESS the victim requests contact, and then only after Children's Court has approved a modification to no violent contact.
-Court waived all applicable costs and surcharges of this case, excluding any applicable mandatory surcharges.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
-Obtain and maintain employment.
-No firearms; weapons.
Received and filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.  Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for June 27, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2 AS AMENDED:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.

Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 2, 2014 at 08:30 am.
